<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-336] portals subsystem no longer exists but used in debug documentation</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-336</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;going though the lustre manual, there are several places where &quot;portals&quot; is described as a subsystem and examples used, but it appears to no longer exist. Sections are 29.2.1.1 and 29.2.2.1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lctl &amp;gt; debug_list subs&lt;br/&gt;
Subsystems: all_subs, undefined, mdc, mds, osc, ost, class, log, llite, rpc, mgmt, lnet, lnd, pinger, filter, echo, ldlm, lov, lquota, osd, lfsck, snapshot, lmv, sec, gss, mgc, mgs, fid, fld&lt;br/&gt;
lctl &amp;gt; debug_list types&lt;br/&gt;
Types: all_types, trace, inode, super, ext2, malloc, cache, info, ioctl, neterror, net, warning, buffs, other, dentry, nettrace, page, dlmtrace, error, emerg, ha, rpctrace, vfstrace, reada, mmap, config, console, quota, sec, lfsck, hsm, snapshot&lt;/p&gt;</description>
